          "body": "The case-law of verses 11-22 is notable for its comprehensiveness. Corpse-impurity transfers by direct touch (19:11), by proximity in a shared tent (19:14), through open vessels left uncovered in a tent where someone dies (19:15), and by touching a slain person, a naturally deceased person, a bone, or even a grave in an open field (19:16). The chapter's impurity-logic models what the New Testament calls the contagion of sin: it spreads through proximity, through contact, through transmission — and left unaddressed, it defiles the dwelling of God. The application law ends with its most sweeping statement: 'Furthermore, anything that the unclean person touches shall be unclean; and the person who touches it shall be unclean until evening' (19:22). Impurity propagates outward in concentric rings. The only thing that stops the spread is the purification water."
