    "intro": "Numbers 19 is the Old Testament's most theologically compact purification ordinance. Its meaning is found not by allegorizing its details but by tracing its argument: a holy God has provided, in advance, the means by which a death-saturated community may remain in his presence. The movements below follow the chapter's two major divisions and their canonical resonances, from the ceremony of preparation (vv.1-10) through the case-law of application (vv.11-22), and into the New Testament resolution Hebrews 9 supplies.",
